* Removed classes

    * Solar_Test_Assert, moved functionality to Solar_Test

* Added classes

    * Solar_Test
    
    * Solar_Test_Suite
    
    * Solar_User_Access and related drivers:  Open, None, File (still
      need Sql, Ini, etc)
    
* General

    * Changed testing methodology away from .phpt to something more
      like SimpleTest/PHPUnit ... Solar_Test.
    
    * Added many new tests, e.g. for Solar_Sql and the drivers.
    
* Solar_App

    * Adds default _preAction() method to check user privileges for the
      page-class and action
    
    * Adds default $errors public property for tracking page errors
    
* Solar_Test_Example

    * Moved support class methods out of test files and into the example
      class (e.g., validation and filter callbacks)

* Solar_Sql

    * BC BREAK:  createIndex() now takes params $table, $name, $unique
      (true/false), and $cols (array of col names) ... previously, took
      $table, $name, $info.
      
    * BC BREAK: query() now always returns boolean true for schema
      manipulation commands (CREATE, ALTER, DROP) ... this is to hide
      inconsistencies in how backends report "number of rows affected".
    
    * Bugfix: query() now honors the array binding-data properly.
    
    * Bugfix: select('statement') now works properly (typo).
    
    * Bugfix: createSequence() now works properly (was passing $this
      instead of $name).
    
    * Bugfix: addColumn now works properly (was omitting the column
      name in the command).
    
* Solar_Sql_Driver_*
    
    * Added driver-specific dropIndex() support.
    
    * Solar_Sql_Driver_Mysql::createSequence() now creates sequence
      tables as InnoDB instead of MyISAM.
      
* Solar_Sql_Table

    * _autoSetup() now massages $this->_idx for proper index info, and
      uses new Solar_Sql::createIndex() params.
    
* Solar_Uri

    * changed "public function pathEncode()" to "protected function
      _pathEncode()"
      
    * When auto-discovering the current URI, it adds "example.com" as a
      dummy host name if $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'] is empty, then removes
      it after parsing the URL.  This is to avoid notices about parsing
      errors.
      
* Solar_User

    * Now has public $access property for Solar_User_Access functions

* Solar_View

    * Added methods getHelperPath(), getTemplatePath()
    
    * The newHelper() method now properly returns a new standalone
      helper, instead of re-instantiating the internal copy of that
      helper.  Also, you can now pass a runtime $config as the second
      parameter.

* Solar_View_Helper_...

    * Anchor: now returns just the HREF if no text specified
    
    * Attribs: now skips empty values, returns '' if no attribs found
    
    * Form:
    
        * Now adds 'descr' to all elements
        
        * Removed $_disable and setDisable() (not honored yet)
        
        * Method addFeedback() is now properly fluent (returns $this)
        
        * Added method getStatus()

    * FormButton: streamlined output concatenation
    
    * FormOptions: no longer indents the options list
    
    * FormRadio: no longer adds extra newline after first hidden value
    
    * FormSelect: streamlined output concatenation
    
    * Image: loads Solar_View_Helper class now
    
    * LinkStylesheet: adds 'media="screen"' attrib if not otherwise
      specified
    
    * Style: adds 'media="screen"' attrib if not otherwise specified
    
    * Timestamp default format is now "Y-m-d\TH:i:s".
    